00:31:55.210 --> 00:31:57.720
Byzantine in drilling
down and working out

00:31:57.720 --> 00:32:00.930
all then of the connections
of the biochemistry

00:32:00.930 --> 00:32:05.038
then of a typical
cell, very complicated.

00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:13.180
Now, let's zoom in
on one part of this.

00:32:13.180 --> 00:32:16.090
If you notice this
circular part right here,

00:32:16.090 --> 00:32:18.228
this is something known
as the citric acid cycle.

00:32:21.370 --> 00:32:23.780
What's interesting about
the citric acid cycle

00:32:23.780 --> 00:32:26.520
is that it's
ubiquitous, from what we

00:32:26.520 --> 00:32:29.170
can tell, across all of life.

00:32:29.170 --> 00:32:32.340
Doesn't matter if you're
bacteria, unicells,

00:32:32.340 --> 00:32:38.080
multi-cells, animals, plants,
we have the citric acid cycle.

00:32:38.080 --> 00:32:41.360
So here's the argument
maybe the TCA cycle

00:32:41.360 --> 00:32:44.910
is an energetic
inevitability, maybe

00:32:44.910 --> 00:32:48.950
the TCA cycle actually
originated before life that we

00:32:48.950 --> 00:32:49.685
know originated.

00:32:53.400 --> 00:32:55.600
Here within the TCA cycle,
what you actually see

00:32:55.600 --> 00:32:58.000
is several different
molecules linked

00:32:58.000 --> 00:33:01.860
to the other in a series
of chemical reactions.

00:33:01.860 --> 00:33:05.610
There is some input here,
mainly pyruvate, acetyl CoA.

00:33:05.610 --> 00:33:07.610
But don't worry about
all those details,

00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:09.790
but if you know a
little bit of biology,

00:33:09.790 --> 00:33:11.570
you should recognize
this, because this

00:33:11.570 --> 00:33:15.280
is one of the key components
of aerobic respiration.

00:33:15.280 --> 00:33:17.000
So if you break down
these sort of sugars

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:18.520
and these sort of
fats or anything,

00:33:18.520 --> 00:33:21.580
ultimately, you're going to
be feeding then molecules

00:33:21.580 --> 00:33:23.720
into the TCA cycle.

00:33:23.720 --> 00:33:27.190
Two Nobel prize is were
given for, effectively,

00:33:27.190 --> 00:33:29.960
the discovery of this.

00:33:29.960 --> 00:33:32.170
Adolf Krebs then
was the one that

00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:34.010
worked out the
full cycle was also

00:33:34.010 --> 00:33:36.140
awarded then the Nobel Prize.

00:33:36.140 --> 00:33:39.870
It is also known
as the Krebs cycle.

00:33:39.870 --> 00:33:42.220
So the core reactions
of the citric acid cycle

00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:47.450
likely existed before cells,
before RNA, before DNA.

00:33:50.100 --> 00:33:53.230
The thinking is that this
is an autocatalytic network,

00:33:53.230 --> 00:33:55.720
an autocatalytic set
then of reactions

00:33:55.720 --> 00:33:57.770
where newly created
molecules, then

00:33:57.770 --> 00:34:00.465
catalyze then the reaction
of the next molecule.

00:34:03.610 --> 00:34:06.320
In general, this is an
energetically favored set

00:34:06.320 --> 00:34:09.920
of reactions, effectively,
it gives off then free energy

00:34:09.920 --> 00:34:13.615
by this set then of
autocatalytic reactions.

00:34:13.615 --> 00:34:14.989
So you can think
of this as a way

00:34:14.989 --> 00:34:19.000
to start creating
order before a lot

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:21.320
of these big biological
macromolecules,

00:34:21.320 --> 00:34:25.620
before cells, before
molecular replication,

00:34:25.620 --> 00:34:30.635
effectively at the start
then, the beginning of life.

00:34:30.635 --> 00:34:33.260
Now, what's interesting is that
the derivatives then of the TCA

00:34:33.260 --> 00:34:36.120
cycle then feed into
that very complicated map

00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:39.020
that I showed you earlier.

00:34:39.020 --> 00:34:42.409
Effectively,
sugars, fatty acids,

00:34:42.409 --> 00:34:46.060
the production of all of
these different molecules,

00:34:46.060 --> 00:34:50.070
nucleic acids, amino acids,
all these various different

00:34:50.070 --> 00:34:52.510
cofactors, critical
things that your body

00:34:52.510 --> 00:34:54.574
needs to complete
all the biochemistry.

00:34:54.574 --> 00:34:56.199
This effectively,
you can think of this

00:34:56.199 --> 00:34:59.030
as kind of like the
fountain of all origination

00:34:59.030 --> 00:35:01.840
of biological biochemistry.

00:35:01.840 --> 00:35:04.530
So the question is, this is
really the first engine then

00:35:04.530 --> 00:35:05.530
of biological synthesis.

00:35:08.630 --> 00:35:12.240
So I'd like you to think of
this as a spinning wheel.

00:35:12.240 --> 00:35:14.460
Every time then this
wheel is cranking around,

00:35:14.460 --> 00:35:16.970
producing not only a bunch
of biological molecules,

00:35:16.970 --> 00:35:24.950
but we're ultimately
creating stored energy.

00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:26.910
Within then the stored
energy ultimately

00:35:26.910 --> 00:35:31.810
is used to produce ATP, which is
effectively how we're powering

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:34.850
then all metabolic reactions.

00:35:34.850 --> 00:35:37.710
So we're creating then a
bunch of biological molecules,

00:35:37.710 --> 00:35:43.140
we're also then creating then
and preserving stored energy.

00:35:43.140 --> 00:35:45.220
What's interesting
is that the rate then

00:35:45.220 --> 00:35:49.060
of the spin of the
TCA cycles influences

00:35:49.060 --> 00:35:54.700
everything, such as how fast
you age, the rate of senescence,

00:35:54.700 --> 00:35:58.600
the risk of cancer, and the
overall organism's energy

00:35:58.600 --> 00:35:59.630
status.

00:35:59.630 --> 00:36:03.910
So how fast the cycle
spins is ultimately related

00:36:03.910 --> 00:36:06.880
to a bunch of other biological
phenomena that we study.

00:36:09.880 --> 00:36:12.990
Now, one of the big
surprises is that there

00:36:12.990 --> 00:36:16.940
are bacteria then on
Earth who actually don't

00:36:16.940 --> 00:36:20.140
rely on an oxygen-rich
environment

00:36:20.140 --> 00:36:25.230
but actually use the TCA cycle,
but they run it in reverse,

00:36:25.230 --> 00:36:27.390
really cool.

00:36:27.390 --> 00:36:30.470
So it runs in reverse,
and it does the opposite.

00:36:30.470 --> 00:36:33.940
So unlike aerobic respiration,
where you breathe in oxygen

00:36:33.940 --> 00:36:37.980
and you breathe out CO2,
if you run it in reverse,

00:36:37.980 --> 00:36:42.370
you can actually suck
in carbon dioxide,

00:36:42.370 --> 00:36:44.960
and you can then create a
bunch of additional organic

00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:48.910
molecules, things like vinegar
