00:40:00.990 --> 00:40:04.700
So the TCA cycle appears
to have originated

00:40:04.700 --> 00:40:09.290
before the origin of cells,
before RNA, and before DNA.

00:40:09.290 --> 00:40:11.870
And it's really this
geothermal energy

00:40:11.870 --> 00:40:14.210
that's effectively
provided the environment

00:40:14.210 --> 00:40:19.080
and the initial chemistry to get
these initial reactions going.

00:40:19.080 --> 00:40:21.430
So remember, if you get
these reactions going,

00:40:21.430 --> 00:40:26.360
all one has to do is simply put
those reactions inside a cell

00:40:26.360 --> 00:40:28.810
in order to contain
it and then control

00:40:28.810 --> 00:40:31.087
the production of these
early biological molecules.

00:40:33.770 --> 00:40:36.580
So if this is correct,
our initial view

00:40:36.580 --> 00:40:39.580
of the start of life
has actually changed.

00:40:39.580 --> 00:40:45.400
What we can actually then see
is that this core metabolism

00:40:45.400 --> 00:40:51.130
of the TCA cycle appears to
have been present at the start.

00:40:53.770 --> 00:40:56.630
Once we have the
ability to create

00:40:56.630 --> 00:40:59.190
some basic biological
molecules associated

00:40:59.190 --> 00:41:01.640
with these autocatalytic
set of reactions,

00:41:01.640 --> 00:41:06.430
somehow, if we then contain and
harness this core metabolism

00:41:06.430 --> 00:41:09.840
within cells, have a
set of genetic material

00:41:09.840 --> 00:41:11.630
in the form of
either DNA or RNA,

00:41:11.630 --> 00:41:15.190
to somehow not only
control those reactions

00:41:15.190 --> 00:41:21.040
but also have natural selection
taking over at that point.

00:41:21.040 --> 00:41:23.780
So if we go from back
to the origin of life

00:41:23.780 --> 00:41:26.280
3.8 billion years
ago, all the way

00:41:26.280 --> 00:41:29.730
to the Cambrian Explosion,
what we actually see

00:41:29.730 --> 00:41:33.050
is this core metabolism
staying put and life

00:41:33.050 --> 00:41:35.720
just building more and
more complexity on top

00:41:35.720 --> 00:41:37.040
of that fundamental core.

00:41:39.850 --> 00:41:41.600
Now, within you,
what's interesting

00:41:41.600 --> 00:41:44.840
is that you run your a cycle
within these organelles

00:41:44.840 --> 00:41:47.050
known as mitochondria.

00:41:47.050 --> 00:41:50.260
What's interesting is that the
mitochondria is essentially

00:41:50.260 --> 00:41:55.420
this long ghost of an
