00:43:30.130 --> 00:43:34.310
is very strong
selection to get big.

00:43:34.310 --> 00:43:38.230
Multicellularity has evolved
multiple times independently.

00:43:38.230 --> 00:43:40.310
So going from
unicellular organisms

00:43:40.310 --> 00:43:42.700
to multicellular
organisms again and again

00:43:42.700 --> 00:43:46.910
appears to offer a
selective advantage.

00:43:46.910 --> 00:43:50.480
So today, the organisms that
we share our planet with

00:43:50.480 --> 00:43:54.920
are actually the largest that
have ever lived on Earth.

