tree, an order of
magnitude larger.

00:44:16.470 --> 00:44:18.270
So why is larger better?

00:44:18.270 --> 00:44:20.760
Throughout time, we
see this increase

00:44:20.760 --> 00:44:23.930
in the size of an organism.

00:44:23.930 --> 00:44:25.600
So if you get big,
you can overcome

00:44:25.600 --> 00:44:29.280
various physical
forces like viscosity.

00:44:29.280 --> 00:44:31.550
If you're very small
and you're in the water,

00:44:31.550 --> 00:44:34.070
that can provide a really
hard situation for you

00:44:34.070 --> 00:44:37.276
in terms of how you go about
your day to day business.

00:44:37.276 --> 00:44:39.400
So if you get bigger, you
can overcome these forces

00:44:39.400 --> 00:44:40.810
like viscosity.

00:44:40.810 --> 00:44:42.500
But also if you're
bigger, you can

00:44:42.500 --> 00:44:46.450
dominate and kind of
maintain larger territories

00:44:46.450 --> 00:44:49.810
and control more
and more resources.

00:44:49.810 --> 00:44:52.740
If you're also bigger, you
can avoid the competition

00:44:52.740 --> 00:44:55.210
of smaller individuals.

00:44:55.210 --> 00:45:00.100
If ' use resources that are
differently available to you,

00:45:00.100 --> 00:45:06.720
being larger often offers
quite a few opportunities.

00:45:06.720 --> 00:45:10.170
If you're bigger, you can
usually do more tasks.

00:45:10.170 --> 00:45:13.600
Larger things tend to have
more different cell types,

00:45:13.600 --> 00:45:17.220
larger things tend to respond
to the environment differently.

00:45:17.220 --> 00:45:21.140
You can also process more and
different types of information.

00:45:21.140 --> 00:45:24.310
But also, if you're
bigger, you live longer.

00:45:24.310 --> 00:45:27.220
And because of which, you often
then have access to resources

00:45:27.220 --> 00:45:28.620
that smaller things don't have.

